.TH "HTMLSCRIPTELEMENT.FETCHPRIORITY" "3JS" "November 7, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLScriptElement.fetchPriority \- HTMLScriptElement: fetchPriority
property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]fetchPriority\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLScriptElement\f[R] interface represents a hint to the browser
indicating how it should prioritize fetching an external script relative
to other external scripts.
It reflects the \f[CR]<script>\f[R] element\(cqs
\f[CR]fetchpriority\f[R] content attribute.
.SH VALUE
A string.
For the permitted values, see the HTML \f[CR]fetchpriority\f[R]
attribute.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]script\f[R] id=\(dqel\(dq type=\(dqmodule\(dq src=\(dqmain.js\(dq fetchpriority=\(dqhigh\(dq></\f[B]script\f[R]>
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] el = document.getElementById(\(dqel\(dq);
console.log(el.fetchPriority); \f[I]// Output: \(dqhigh\(dq\f[R]
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]HTMLImageElement.fetchPriority\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
